article.description: The college basketball game between Seattle and Eastern Washington scheduled for Tuesday evening has been postponed because of a fierce wind storm in the Spokane region.
article.headline: Eastern Washington's college basketball game postponed
article.linkText: Eastern Washington's college basketball game postponed
article.story:
CHENEY, Wash. --  The college basketball game between Seattle and Eastern Washington scheduled for Tuesday evening has been postponed because of a fierce wind storm in the Spokane region.

Sustained winds of more than 40 mph, gusting to more than 60 mph, have created dangerous travel conditions across Eastern Washington.

Eastern Washington University said the game will be played in Cheney on Wednesday at 12:30 p.m.

The Seattle University team is staying at a hotel in Spokane on Tuesday evening.
